---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
import authors from '../../data/authors.json';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'About', href: '/about' },
  { label: 'Our Authors', href: '/about/authors' }
];
---

<Layout 
  title="Our Authors & Editorial Standards | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Meet the cannabis compliance professionals and editorial experts behind Maine Dispensary Guide. Learn about our content review process and author credentials."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <style>

  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .editorial-process {
    background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.04);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .process-steps {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .process-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-number {
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .step-content h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .step-content p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .author-grid {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .authors-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .author-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 1.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease;
  }

  .author-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(13, 78, 80, 0.08);
  }

  .author-photo {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .author-photo img {
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .photo-placeholder {
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, var(--color-accent) 100%);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .initials {
    color: white;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
  }

  .author-info {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .author-name {
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .author-role {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .author-bio {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .author-credentials h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .author-credentials ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .author-credentials li {
    background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .linkedin-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .linkedin-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .photo-infrastructure {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: rgba(13, 78, 80, 0.03);
    border-radius: 1rem;
  }

  .photo-status {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .status-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .status-icon {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .trust-for-outreach {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(13, 78, 80, 0.04) 0%, rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.08) 100%);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }

  .trust-for-outreach h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .trust-for-outreach p {
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: var(--color-accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .author-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .author-credentials ul {
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }

</style>
<div class="article-header">
    <h1>Our Authors & Editorial Standards</h1>
    <p class="lead">Every piece of content on Maine Dispensary Guide is written by knowledgeable professionals and reviewed for accuracy.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="editorial-process">
    <h2>Editorial Review Process</h2>
    <p>Maine cannabis regulations are complex and change frequently. That's why our content undergoes a multi-layer review process before publication.</p>
    
    <div class="process-steps">
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Primary Research</h3>
          <p>Our editorial team researches directly from Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP) sources, state statutes, and municipal regulations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Expert Drafting</h3>
          <p>Content is drafted by team members with direct experience in Maine cannabis licensing and operations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Compliance Review</h3>
          <p>A Maine-licensed compliance professional reviews all regulatory content for accuracy and currency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Regular Updates</h3>
          <p>We monitor regulatory changes and update content when laws or OCP guidance evolve.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Callout title="Our Commitment to Accuracy" type="success">
    For YMYL (Your Money Your Life) cannabis content, we take E-E-A-T (Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, Trustworthiness) seriously. Our review process ensures that when you base business decisions on our content, you can trust the information.
  </Callout>

  <section class="author-grid">
    <h2>Meet Our Team</h2>
    <div class="authors-container">
      {authors.map((author) => (
        <div class="author-card" id={author.id}>
          <div class="author-photo">
            {author.photo ? (
              <img src={author.photo} alt={author.name} />
            ) : (
              <div class="photo-placeholder">
                <span class="initials">
                  {author.name.split(' ').map(n => n[0]).join('').slice(0, 2)}
                </span>
              </div>
            )}
          </div>
          <div class="author-info">
            <h3 class="author-name">{author.name}</h3>
            <p class="author-role">{author.role}</p>
            <p class="author-bio">{author.bio}</p>
            <div class="author-credentials">
              <h4>Credentials</h4>
              <ul>
                {author.credentials.map((cred) => (
                  <li>{cred}</li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
            {author.linkedin && (
              <a href={author.linkedin} class="linkedin-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Connect on LinkedIn →
              </a>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="photo-infrastructure">
    <h2>Author Photo Program</h2>
    <p>We're building toward full author attribution with photos. As our team grows, each author will have a dedicated profile photo to strengthen trust signals for our readers and outreach partners.</p>
    <div class="photo-status">
      <div class="status-item">
        <span class="status-icon">📷</span>
        <span>Infrastructure ready — photos can be added per-author</span>
      </div>
      <div class="status-item">
        <span class="status-icon">🔗</span>
        <span>LinkedIn integration available when profiles are complete</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="trust-for-outreach">
    <h2>Built for Professional Outreach</h2>
    <p>This author infrastructure exists for a reason: when we reach out to Maine.gov, the Maine Chamber of Commerce, or academic institutions for partnerships and backlinks, we're not sending anonymous content.</p>
    <p>Our bylined, reviewed content demonstrates the kind of professional credibility that earns links from authoritative sources.</p>
    <a href="/about/our-team" class="btn-secondary">Back to Our Team Overview →</a>
  </section>

<section class="faq-section">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>What are the key compliance requirements?</h3>
    <p>Consult the Maine OCP for current requirements. Key areas include licensing, inventory tracking via METRC, advertising restrictions, and product testing requirements.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>How do I renew my license?</h3>
    <p>License renewal requirements are established by the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy. Submit renewal applications before expiration and ensure all documentation is current.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>What penalties apply for violations?</h3>
    <p>Penalties vary by violation type and severity. The OCP maintains a penalty schedule that includes fines, license suspension, and revocation for serious or repeated violations.</p>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
